comment._content: Darn it - flickr is not letting me scribble on some photos - the name on the boat is guessable as 'OCTOPUS' which is mentioned in this 1902 SMH article about ongoing cleansing of the Darling Harbour wharves - trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/article/14456489. See also State Records NSW version in b&w not sepia - www.flickr.com/photos/state-records-nsw/7558808228/
